main event: Multiple witnesses reported sighting an unidentified object in Ventnor, New Jersey in April 1967.
interesting points: The object was observed for approximately 9 minutes by one witness and only visible for 9 seconds by another., The object was described as moving in a straight course but conflicting accounts existed about its actual path., Witnesses reported the object did not obstruct any other objects or pass behind clouds., Observers described the object as bright with colors including white and red., The report concluded with 'Other (CONFLICTING DATA)' as no clear identification was made.
witness description: one adult male age 32 and one young female age 10
